						               													<description>Neon is a tile placement game for 2 to 4 players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Everyone starts with 3 tiles and one mission card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On your turn, either draw 2 tiles and place up to three tiles on the table, building a collective set of tiles, in such a way that all the sides match and are legally connected OR draw 3 Mission cards, keep one and discard two.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A mission card shows a combination to be created on the Neon pattern on the table.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;If a pattern on the Neon shows what your mission card asks, you score points!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When a player complete a Mission card, he or she gets a Conquer card. Conquer cards allow players to change tiles already on the table, changing everything!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends as soon as anyone completes four Mission cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
